=99s folks are rightly unhappy with some of my opinions about the auction h=
ouse, so let=E2=80=99s give them
the credit they deserve here. The work is a late example of one of the arti=
st=E2=80=99s most famous subjects, but the painter never signed it. It=E2=
=80=99s from the large trove of late waterlily paintings that he never let =
out of the studio. (His heirs stamped it with his signature, and so the art=
